<p>I'm having a problem with the mousover effect for the tipstyle feature on CFChart. </p>  <p>When you hover over a part of the chart, it shows the TipStyle way up in the upper left hand part of the browser window. Even though the charge is in the cente of the page.</p>  <p><a href="http://i.stack.imgur.com/bXCvI.png" rel="nofollow"><img src="http://i.stack.imgur.com/bXCvI.png" alt="Screenshot"></a></p>  <p>For the above screenshot, I am hovering over the chart in the lower right hand corner of the page and you can see that the tipstyle is in the upper left hand part of the page.</p>  <p>Server is running CF9 and this happens in Google Chrome &amp; Firefox. Can this be fixed?</p>  <p>Here is my chart code:</p>  <pre><code>&lt;cfoutput&gt;         &lt;cfchart show3d="yes" format="png" showlegend="yes"&gt;             &lt;cfchartseries type="pie" serieslabel="#activeTechnicians.displayName#" seriescolor="yellow" datalabelstyle="value"&gt;                  &lt;cfloop query="activeTechnicians"&gt;                     &lt;!---Query all closed tickets from start year ---&gt;                     &lt;cfquery name="comparison" datasource="#datasource#"&gt;&lt;!---Open tickets from chosen year where technician is active ---&gt;                     select *                     from closed_tickets                     where MONTH(closed_date) = &lt;CFQUERYPARAM Value="#technician_comparison_month#"&gt; AND YEAR(closed_date) = &lt;CFQUERYPARAM Value="#thisYear#"&gt; AND technician_id = &lt;CFQUERYPARAM Value="#activeTechnicians.id#"&gt;                     order by technician_name                     &lt;/cfquery&gt;                   &lt;cfchartdata item="#activeTechnicians.displayName#" value="#comparison.recordcount#"&gt;                &lt;/cfloop&gt;             &lt;/cfchartseries&gt;         &lt;/cfchart&gt;               &lt;/cfoutput&gt; </code></pre>